  "text": "In this paper we demonstrate that TFs can accomplish this goal by exploiting the modal properties of the narrowing waveguide. As the taper narrows, guided modes are gradually coupled with the environment enabling the probe to collect light along an extended region with a more homogenous collection profile compared to standard FFs ( Fig. 2 a, b, Fig. 3, 4) . Given a constant output power density at the active optical surface, FFs are better suited to collect signal from shallow brain regions adjacent to the fiber facet [CITATION_1] .",
